%set(name,perl)
%set(description,"This is an optional extension which allows the execution of arbitrary perl code in SMX.

It can be quite efficient if the correct functions are export'ed as a part of global initialization of the web server.

The perl function \"output\" returns the string to the SMX engine.  Don't use print for this.  We *will* be taking STDOUT and incorporating it ... so don't rely on STDOUT do do anything until that happens.

The perl function \"export\" causes the named function to be exported to SMX.  With an optional second argument the function can be renamed.   This is a way of exposing perl functions in SMX.

Using the %%perl function is many times more efficient than using %%exec.")
%set(syntax,"%%module\(libextperl.so\)

%%perl\(&lt;perl code here&gt;\)")
%set(example,"%%module\(libextperl.so\)
%%perl\(use Digest::MD5; 
      export\(\"Digest::MD5::md5_hex\",\"md5_hex\"\);
\)
%%md5_hex\(1\) equals %%md5\(1\)

--- result ---

c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b equals c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b")
%set(seealso,module)
%set(authorip,69.134.54.59)
